{"default_url":null,"content":{"state":0,"taskInstructions":null,"references":[],"isTaskInstructionsVisible":true,"isCommentMandatory":false,"fields":[],"masterFinding":{"id":17059909,"exploitInstructions":"","verificationInstructions":"<b>Verification Instructions</b>\n\nAttempt to send the same SAML response to the application twice. If the application provides a new session for the second submission, it is vulnerable to replay attacks.\n\n<b>Reporting Requirements</b>\n<ol><li>Send two submissions of the same SAML message to the application</li>\n<li>Show that the application responds with valid sessions for both messages</li>\n</ol>\n","remediationInstructions":"Do not accept the same SAML token more than once.\n\nSAML messages should contain a unique AssertionID for each assertion. The application should track these AssertionIDs to ensure valid messages are only accepted once.\n","name":"SAML - Token Replay","sourceId":"M:b3aab28f-8002-e711-80f5-ecf4bbd04083","severity":"Low","businessImpact":"SAML replay may allow a malicious user to gain unauthorized access to protected resources by replaying a previous SAML token.","description":"It is possible to replay SAML tokens to gain multiple sessions.\n"}}}